a bit more in touch with the game.  But when I get email with the names of lawyers attached, it tends to get my attention.  What in the HELL is going on here, kids????<br><br>Let me be blunt.  I don't really care who likes who, or who stalks who in Freeport, or who dicked who out of 1000 plat. You can rip one another up one side and down the other daily.  But for the love of God, keep the G-A-M-E in perspective.  Do not use this board or Everquest as an extension of your personal vendettas or fetishes in relation to one another!<br><br>For better or worse MY name is on the user agreement that brought this board into existence, and while I am quite confident that my legal culpability in any matters relating to it would be nil, the sheer hassle of dealing with lawyers is way more than I should be asked to contend with!<br><br>So....what is Shaelyn to do?<br><br>1.  Ignore this until some joker in a pinstripe Armani knocks on my door or I get a summons?  <br><br>2.  Ban everyone involved in the issue? (you know who you are)<br><br>3.  Delete the offending threads and try to forget this ever happened?<br><br>4.  Shut down the board forever?<br><br>What is it going to be?  For now it is going to be #3...and the first person who opens their cake-hole to piss and moan about it is going to find out how fast #2 can happen.  I hate to be a hardass, but I have to be.<br><br>I have been very pleased by the level of support this board has gotten, and 98% of the users have no involvement in this matter.  Raene has done a fine job as your day to day admin, but this issue has gone too far and she need not deal with it either.  <br><br>Thanks for reading this....and if it offends you in any way:<br><br>TOUGH!! <br><br><br><br><br> <p><table border="1" bordercolor="#000000" cellpadding="5" bgcolor="#0066cc"><tr><center><td bgcolor="#2C522C"><center><strong><font face="Ariel, sans-serif" color="#D0FED0">Shaelyn Feather</font><br><font color="#2CF42C">