another.  Maybe the coffee was too hot at the gas station.  Maybe the loud music rattled the urn containing the ashes of their dearly departed Uncle Elmer off the mantle and caused emotional trauma.  Whatever the case, lawsuits are filed by the truckload every single day.<br><br>When it comes to the internet, the already gray area of civil and criminal liability gets even fuzzier.  Let's all be logical and look at this from a hypothetical standpoint for a moment.  Suppose the litigation in question was filed.  Suppose I had chosen to keep the thread in place after being asked by the litigator to remove it.  What types of things might happen?<br><br>I was not intimately aware of the facts of the dispute in question.  Had a minor been stalked?  Propositioned online?  Had meaningful threats been made?  I saw nothing like that in the thread I personally deleted, but you have to realize that I had NO way of knowing the full scope of this.<br><br>Now, you tell me what is easier and safer for me, as a person, to do.<br><br>1.  Ignore the request to remove the thread and write off the legal issues as many of you are so quick to do? <br><br>2. Delete a more or less meaningless thread, and thus remove any possible liability on the part of myself and my moderators?<br><br>I think any of you that truly value your real life commitments would come pretty quickly to the same conclusion I did.  Is it more important to remove a risk to my personal, real world life or to avoid offending a few posters on a message board that I have sunk a couple hundred bucks of my own cash into?<br><br>I can tell you right here and right now that I place my career, my family, and myself waaaaay over this board.  If you cannot understand that now, I hope someday you will.<br><br>It has been my ongoing policy (supported by my mods and most posters) to forbid ALL personal, real life information from being revealed by a poster about another poster, regardless of intent.  This is called Covering Your Ass..and when minors are involved it becomes ten times more important.<br><br>So, while I take no sides in this dispute, I also do not apologize for the actions of myself or my moderators.  You can post about EQ and the Taliban, and egg cookers, and Jesus Christ for all I care.  But don't do things that place the life, privacy, or security of others at risk.  Simple enough I think.<br><br>Thanks again for all your kind support!<br><br> <p><table border="1" bordercolor="#000000" cellpadding="5" bgcolor="#0066cc"><tr><center><td bgcolor="#2C522C"><center><strong><font face="Ariel, sans-serif" color="#D0FED0">Shaelyn Feather</font><br><font color="#2CF42C">Grand Pooh Bah of:</font></strong><br><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/bthecrossroadstavern8833" target="_top"><FONT face="Ariel" color="#2CF42C">Crossroads:Raves, Raids, Rants for Zeb Server!</FONT></a><br><strong><font face="Ariel, sans-serif" color="#D0FED0">Requiem of Souls</font></strong></td><td bgcolor="#2C522C"><div align="center"><strong><a href="http://2amstudios.com/eq/" target="_top"><font face="Ariel, sans-serif" color="#D0FED0">Zebuxoruk</font></a></strong><br><strong><a href="mailto:cbuswell@ascpl.lib.oh.us"><font face="Ariel, sans-serif" size="1" color="#D0FED0">E-mail</a></font></strong></div></td></tr></table> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uraene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raene</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Battle Druid, Artist</span><br>  Posts: 452<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/01 6:15:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroads